This is an article as found on the German Wikipedia. This pastor is noteworthy not only for the German speaking Wikipedia encyclopaedia. Which is why I have submitted it to the English encyclopaedia.
[[WP:AES|←]]Created page with ''''Volkhard Spitzer''' ([[August 12]], [[1943]] in [[Göppingen]]) is a German [[Pastor]] of the Christlichen Zentrums Berlin (CZB).  == Life == Volkhard Spitzer...'
I edited basic grammatically errors and brought clarity to the text through grammatical fixes that help the reader understand the content.

The architectural description of the interior courtyards as being described as "interiors" was misleading in that "interior" generally would refer to the interior rooms of the structure. This edit brings clarity that the inner courtyard facades are also modern with the exception of the Schlüterhof.
This brings clarity to this sentence. It is not grammatically correct to say that the the building was demolished to "make place". Make room or in order is better.

This brings clarity to this sentence. The art museum was not located in the 19th Century palace because the palace was built mainly during the 18th Century. It should say that the museum was housed in the palace in the 19th Century.
Fixing the grammar mistake of with and replacing it with "and".
Added the hyperlink prefix
Adding the source to the text for the claim regarding the Crown Prince's depiction in the mosaic on the vault.

I edited this line to bring more clarity to the mention of the mosaic on the vault of the memorial hall. There is a depiction of the future crown prince in the line of "kings" of Prussia. He never became king.
Additional edits to bring clarity to the fact that both airlines mentioned as having headquarters in this locality are no longer operational.
I changed the verb tense in two cases to reflect the fact that Air Berlin is no longer an operating airline.
I added the word "former" before the mention of "Berlin-Tegel Airport" as this airport no longer exists.
This provides a source for the missing source regarding the shooting of a protestor during the 1960s in Berlin. It clearly provides details as to the content of the protest.
I simply removed the unnecessary parentheses around the source quote.

I added the source for this claim which is an article in German that explains the amount of destruction from the air raids during this time. The area around the church mentioned in the article is considered the city centre of Berlin where most buildings were totally destroyed.
The Kempinski Hotel on Kurfürstendamm has been renamed Hotel Bristol Berlin. This edit reflects the current status of the hotel at the boulevard.
This edit adds the additional role of school's "Managing Director" to the current German principal.
